The paper proposes a new method for Positive-Unlabeled Learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper discusses the use of classifiers, neural networks, and ensembles of trees, which are commonly used in the subfields of machine learning such as artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and data science (cs.DS). The paper also discusses risk estimation, which is a common topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, since the main focus of the paper is on machine learning, we believe that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category.
